## Frontend Excellence Protocol

Selling a product right is EVERYTHING. The frontend is not "UI" — it is the product's first impression, its personality, its proof of quality. Every pixel communicates craft.

### Design DNA (from Linear + Dimension + Dala inspirations)

- **Dark-mode-first**: Near-black canvas (#08090a to #0a0a0a), cool grays, one signature accent color
- **Whisper-weight display type**: Large headlines at weight 200-400 with tight negative tracking (-0.03em+)
- **Single accent color rationed**: One chromatic accent per screen (acid lime, indigo, or violet) — never decorative, always functional
- **Glassmorphism over shadows**: Depth through backdrop-blur and translucency, not shadow stacks
- **Pill-shaped interactions**: 9999px radius for buttons, badges, nav elements
- **Instrument-panel density**: Compact, information-rich, every pixel earns its place
- **1px hairline borders**: Surfaces defined by edges, not fills

### Animation Requirements (MANDATORY on every interactive element)

**Libraries**: Framer Motion (motion) + GSAP for complex sequences

| Element | Animation | Duration | Easing |
|---------|-----------|----------|--------|
| Page transitions | Fade + subtle Y translate (8px) | 300ms | ease-out |
| Cards appearing | Scale from 0.96 + opacity 0→1 | 250ms | spring(1, 80, 10) |
| Button hover | Scale 1.02 + subtle glow | 150ms | ease-out |
| Button press | Scale 0.97 | 100ms | ease-in |
| Sidebar expand | Width animate + content fade | 200ms | ease-out |
| Modal open | Backdrop fade + content scale from 0.95 | 250ms | spring |
| Toast notification | Slide in from right + fade | 300ms | spring(1, 70, 12) |
| Agent status pulse | Infinite scale pulse 1→1.15→1 | 2000ms | ease-in-out |
| Loading skeleton | Shimmer gradient sweep left→right | 1500ms | linear, infinite |
| Data streaming | Character-by-character reveal | 20ms per char | linear |
| Progress indicators | Width animate with spring overshoot | 400ms | spring |
| Tab switch | Active indicator slides with spring | 300ms | spring(1, 85, 12) |

### Micro-Interactions (the details that make users say "this feels premium")

- **Hover states on EVERYTHING interactive**: Subtle scale, opacity shift, or border color change
- **Focus rings**: Animated focus ring that expands outward (not just a static border)
- **Scroll-triggered reveals**: Elements fade/slide in as they enter viewport (IntersectionObserver + motion)
- **Number counters**: Animate from 0 to value when entering viewport
- **Cursor trails on dashboard**: Subtle cursor-follow glow on the agent visualization
- **Message streaming**: Real-time character reveal (not pop-in) for agent messages
- **Skeleton loading**: Every async operation shows a shimmer skeleton, never a blank space
- **State transitions**: Never jump between states — always animate (empty → loading → content → error)
- **Drag interactions**: Cards/items that can be reordered with spring physics
- **Pull-to-refresh**: Rubber-band overscroll feedback

### Sound Design (subtle, satisfying, optional — user can mute)

| Action | Sound | Character |
|--------|-------|-----------|
| Task submitted | Soft "whoosh" (200ms) | Confidence — something launched |
| Agent joined room | Subtle "ping" (150ms) | Presence — someone arrived |
| Review passed | Satisfying "ding" (300ms) | Success — clean, bright |
| Review failed | Low "thud" (200ms) | Attention needed — not alarming |
| Task complete | Rising tone sequence (400ms) | Achievement — progression |
| Approval needed | Gentle chime (250ms) | Decision point — soft urgency |

**Implementation**: Web Audio API with pre-loaded buffers. Volume at 30% default. Mute toggle in settings. Never play sound without user having interacted first (browser autoplay policy).

### Loading States (never show blank space)

```
1. Skeleton → shimmer gradient animation
2. Pulse placeholder → subtle opacity breathing (0.4 → 0.7 → 0.4)
3. Progress bar → spring-physics width with overshoot
4. Spinner → custom SVG with stroke-dasharray animation
5. Content streaming → character reveal with cursor blink
```

### Layout Principles

- **Generous whitespace**: Let content breathe — 80-120px between major sections
- **Information density**: Dense where data lives (tables, feeds), spacious where attention matters (hero, CTAs)
- **Grid discipline**: 4px base unit, 8px column gaps, 1200px max content width
- **Mobile-first responsive**: Stack gracefully, never break
- **Sticky elements**: Navigation, agent status bar, approval queue — always accessible
- **Z-index discipline**: Background(0) → Content(10) → Sticky(20) → Modal(30) → Toast(40) → Tooltip(50)

### What "Selling the Product" Means in Practice

The dashboard is not a data dump. It is a **narrative**:
- The live agent feed should feel like watching a TEAM work (not reading logs)
- Agent status cards should BREATHE — subtle animations showing life/activity
- The task pipeline should have FLOW — visual indication of movement/progress
- Memory accumulation should feel like GROWTH — numbers counting up, graphs filling
- The approval queue should feel IMPORTANT — cards with weight, not flat lists

### Anti-Patterns (absolutely forbidden)

- Static pages with no animation → dead product
- Jarring state changes without transitions → amateur
- Loading spinners without context → anxiety-inducing
- Flat unstyled tables → data dump, not product
- Default browser focus rings → lazy
- No hover states → feels broken
- Instant content pop-in → cheapens the experience
- Sound that plays without user consent → hostile
